OL,6,F"There were no designated walkways,
OL,7,Fvehicles were criss-crossing it on a
OL,8,Fregular basis and what happened was
OL,9,Fquite clearly a significant risk
OL,10,Fbecause every time that vehicle was
OL,11,Ffilled and moving forward the driver,
OL,12,Fhowever experienced he was, could not
OL,13,Fsee ahead of him and there was a blind
OL,14,Fspot at the front of the vehicle."
OL,16,FJessica Brooke, Mr Brooke's widow
OL,17,Fsaid: "He was a really great father, a
OL,18,Fgreat husband.
